The plugin allows you to run different mod or sets of plugins on the same server. Each mod can have different set of plugins, different advertisements, different maps and even different motd. players can type /rtv to rock the vote for next mod and next map or can type /votemap or /votemod to rock the vote for map or mod respectively.

Features :-
-rtv
-votemap
-votemod
-blockmod
-different motd for each mod
-different advertisement for each mod

Installation :-

-Extract the .rar file in addons/amxmodx folder.
-Restart the server.

Installation of mods:-

-Add a new line in addons/amxmodx/configs/multimod/multimod.ini file with the format "MOD Name" "Mod Tag".
 example:- "Gun game" "gg"
-Create those files for each mod in addons/amxmodx/configs/multimod folder
 example:- modtag-plugins.ini, modtag-maps.ini, modtag-cfg.cfg, modtag-ads.ini, modtag-motd.txt.

modtag-plugins.ini: plugin list to be loaded for the mod (you must include multimod.amxx, admin plugins, menu plugins, mod specific plugins, etc).
modtag-maps.ini: maps list for the mod.
modtag-cfg.cfg: custom cvars and values for the mod.
modtag-motd.txt: motd for the mod.
modtag-ads.ini: custom advertisements for the mod.

Cvars :-
All cvar's are included in addons/amxmodx/configs/multimod/multimod.cfg file

Spoiler Hide
// Chat / Menu prefix
mm_prefix "[AMXX]"

// Enable / disable changing hostname according to mod
mm_hostname_enable "1"

// Hostname format ( work's only when mm_hostname_enable is set to 1 )
// use %modname% for current mod name
mm_hostname "Multi-Mod [%modname%] server"

// Different advertisement for each mod
mm_mod_advertisement "1"

// Interval of time between advertisement ( time differenc between two different ads ) in seconds
mm_mod_advertisement_interval "40.0"

// Enable / Disable mod Blocking
mm_blockmod_enable "1"

// Block mod admin flag
// Admins with only specified flag will be able to block / unblock mod, change current mod to block mod
mm_blockmod_adminflag "l"

// Enable / Disable Mod Motd file
// If enable $moddir/addons/amxmodx/configs/multimod/$modname-motd.txt will be consider as motd file
// If disable $moddir/motd.txt will be consider as motd file
mm_motd_enable "1"

// Rtv Mod
// 0 = disable Rtv feature
// 1 = Normal Rtv Mod
// 2 = Advanced Rtv mod ( votemod and votemap )
mm_rtv_mode "1"

// Normal Rtv Mod
mm_rtv_minplayers "3"
mm_rtv_mintime "8"
mm_rtv_max "8"
mm_rtv_percent "30"

// Advanced Rtv mod ( votemod and votemap )
// Votemod
mm_votemod_enable "1"
mm_votemod_minplayers "3"
mm_votemod_mintime "8"
mm_votemod_max "8"
mm_votemod_percent "30"

// Votemap
mm_votemap_enable "1"
mm_votemap_minplayers "3"
mm_votemap_mintime "8"
mm_votemap_max "8"
mm_votemap_percent "30"

// Mod Extend Limit
// -1 to disable extend mod
mm_rtv_maxextend "1"


Say Commands (work with "/" or without "/" ) :-

nextmod - show next mod
lastmod - show last mod
currentmod - show currently running mod
mods - shows a menu with all mods installed on the server
nextmap - show nextmap ( requries nextmap.amxx, mapchooser.amxx plugins running )
lastmap - show lastmap
maps - shows a menu with all maps installed for currently running mod
rtv - rock the vote for mod and map ( if mm_rtv_mode is set to 1)
votemap - rock the vote for map ( if mm_rtv_mode is set to 2)
votemod - rock the vote for mod ( if mm_rtv_mode is set to 2)

I have been developing / working on these plugin since 7 months and have develop it to run the server with less space and less downloads for the clients.
